The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 Mumbai, Jan. 3 (PTI): Haj pilgrims on board an Air India flight from Jeddah refused to leave the plane after it was diverted to Mumbai from fog-hit Delhi and confined its cabin crew for 15 hours to protest the detour, an employee association said.          
	The unruly passengers blocked the exits and prevented the security and traffic from coming on board and/or deplaning the other passengers into the parked buses, the All India Cabin Crew Association said in a statement. The passengers did not let anyone get off for 15 hours until 9.40 this morning, the association said. The passengers denied having confined the cabin crew.                  
	 Chennai (PTI): Six Afghan nationals were detained at Anna International airport in Chennai on Sunday for allegedly carrying fake passports, officials said. All the six passengers had come from Nepal to Chennai and were about to board a Malaysia-bound flight. The passengers told the officials that they had obtained the passports from Nepal. All of them were handed over to police.                  
	 Muzaffarnagar (PTI): An army jawan allegedly committed suicide on Sunday after being pressured by his parents to leave his wife as she belonged to the same. sub-caste (gotra).                   
	 Tirupati (PTI): Six pilgrims from Lucknow and their driver were killed and four others injured when the van in which they were travelling collided with a lorry in Andhra Pradesh on Sunday, police said. The vehicle carrying the 10-member family was headed from Chennai to the shrine of Lord Venkateswara at Tirupati.                  
	 London (PTI): Shilpa Shetty is planning a wedding reception at the House of Commons, The Daily Mirror has reported. The celebrations have been organised partly by MP Keith Vaz. Shilpa recently married NRI millionaire Raj Kundra in India.                                                                                                                                              
